<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 08 at 4:08AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Plymouth,
Bristol, Newport and east central Bristol Counties through 500 AM
EDT...
At 407 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles south of Newport, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
New Bedford, Fall River, Plymouth, Taunton, Dartmouth, Bridgewater,
Newport, Marion, Middleborough, Wareham, Norton, Somerset,
Portsmouth, Middletown, Fairhaven, Swansea, Tiverton, Westport,
Raynham and Rehoboth.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Get indoors when you hear thunder. Do not resume outdoor activities
until at least 30 minutes after the storm has passed.</instruction>
